01/02/2004
BOSTON, United States -- Turkish Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan delivered a speech at Harvard University on Saturday (31 January), the last day of his visit to the United States. He stressed that a civilian government is in power in Turkey and that the army fulfils its duties as defined in the constitution.
Meanwhile, the Turkish Council of Ministers approved the protocols concerning the NATO membership of seven new countries in NATO: Bulgaria, Romania, Slovenia, Latvia, Lithuania, Estonia and Slovakia. The protocols were published on Saturday in the <I>Official Gazette </I>. (Anadolu Agency, NTV, TRT 2 - 31/01/04)
